  },
  {
    question: "What are Ontario Building Code requirements for legal basements?",
    answer: "Legal basements require: minimum 6'5\" ceiling height, egress windows (3.8 sq ft opening minimum), separate entrance, 1-hour fire separation, interconnected smoke/CO alarms, proper ventilation, approved electrical/plumbing, and all necessary permits and inspections."
  },
  {
    question: "What is the ROI on legal basement apartments in Toronto?",
    answer: "Legal basement apartments offer excellent ROI: rental income $1,900-2,500/month, property value increase 10-20% ($108,000-200,000+), typical payback 3-5 years. Legal status enables legitimate income for mortgages, tax benefits, and 20-30% higher rent than illegal units."
