  {
    question: "What makes a basement 'legal' in Ontario?",
    answer: "A legal basement must meet Ontario Building Code requirements including: minimum 6'5\" ceiling height, proper egress windows (minimum 3.8 sq ft opening), separate entrance, fire-rated separation from main dwelling, interconnected smoke/CO alarms, proper ventilation, and approved electrical/plumbing systems. Additionally, you need proper permits and must pass all city inspections."
