  {
    question: "Do I need underpinning for a legal basement?",
    answer: "Underpinning is required if your current ceiling height is below 6'5\" (1.95m). Most Toronto homes built before 1960 have 6-6.5' basements requiring underpinning. We lower the floor by 8-16\" to achieve 7-8' finished height. This also allows for proper insulation, plumbing, and creates a more comfortable living space."
  },
  {
    question: "What are egress window requirements?",
    answer: "Every bedroom needs an egress window for emergency escape. Requirements: minimum 3.8 sq ft (0.35 m²) opening area, no dimension less than 15\" (380mm), sill height maximum 1.5m above floor, window well must be 760mm (30\") deep minimum with ladder if over 900mm deep. We handle all measurements and ensure full NBC compliance."
