    question: "Can I do some work myself to save money?",
    answer: "While you can do finishing work like painting and flooring, all structural, plumbing, and electrical work must be done by licensed professionals for permit approval. DIY work often fails inspection, causing costly delays. We offer flexible packages where you can handle finishing touches while we manage all permit-required work."
  },
  {
    question: "What happens if my illegal basement gets reported?",
    answer: "The city can issue compliance orders requiring immediate vacancy, levy fines up to $54,000, and you may face lawsuits from tenants for illegal rental. Your insurance may deny claims, and you cannot claim rental income or expenses on taxes. Legalization protects you from all these risks."
  },
  {
    question: "Are there any rebates or grants available?",
    answer: "Yes! Canada Greener Homes Grant: up to $5,400 for insulation and windows. Toronto Multi-Residential Improvement Program: low-interest loans. CMHC Secondary Suite Financing: up to $43,000. HST New Housing Rebate: up to $32,000. We help you apply for all applicable programs."
